2026-05-30 — DHT11 native 1-Wire on ESP32-S3: `noInterrupts()` during ~5ms can cause WiFi packet loss if the DHT11 is slow to respond. Timeouts must be generous (300µs first pulse, 120µs subsequent, 80µs bits). The retry (1 after 1s) is essential because the DHT11 can fail intermittently due to bus noise. The final checksum discards corrupted data.

2026-05-30 — Web UI pin mapping redesign: grouping inputs by peripheral (NFC, HC-SR04, DHT11) in individual cards is more usable than a flat grid. Each card has a Lucide icon, distinctive color (cyan/yellow/green), and current values inline in the label. Number inputs must have `-moz-appearance:textfield` to hide spinners in Firefox.

2026-05-31 — Telnet auth synchronized with webPass. Legacy `TELNET_PASSWORD` no longer used; `terminal.cpp` and `tareas.cpp` now check `telnetAutenticado` against `webPass`. 5min inactivity timeout added.

2026-05-30 — WebSocket buffer overflow: NEVER do `data[len] = 0` in an ESPAsyncWebSocket callback. The `data` buffer is exactly `len` bytes, there is no space for the null terminator. Always use `malloc(len+1)` + `memcpy` + `cmd[len] = 0`. Using strlen/strdup on the unterminated buffer can read garbage memory and cause heap corruption.

2026-05-30 — `getLocalTime()` on ESP32 is thread-safe but can access timezone data in flash, which requires flash cache. If called on every loop iteration (~1ms), it can cause cache contention with other flash operations (LittleFS, OTA). Always throttle NTP function calls with a millis()-based guard.

2026-05-30 — preview_setup.html is a demo/preview version without backend logic (simulated goStep3, no fetch). Always integrate visual changes from the preview while keeping the real file logic in web_pages.cpp. Preview changes are exclusively CSS/HTML/UX; backend JS (iniciarConexion, pollStatus, scanNetworks, ejecutarReset) must not be touched.

2026-05-29 — When changing pins from `#define` to `extern int`, any code that uses those symbols at compile time (arrays, templates) can break. MFRC522 requires pins in its constructor, forcing a refactor to pointer. SPI.begin() also takes the CS pin as runtime uint8_t, which is compatible with int.

2026-05-29 — Preferences NVS on ESP32: each namespace is independent. `prefs.clear()` only clears keys from the open namespace, does not affect other namespaces. This allows `hwconfig`, `webcred` and `zenithmc` (WiFi) as separate namespaces without interference.

2026-05-29 — The original captive portal (wifi_setup_html) used `#define` pins for the HTML layout. With the change to runtime, default values are shown as placeholders in screen 0. Field names in the HTML (nfcRst, nfcSs, etc.) must match the JSON keys that the backend expects in `/api/wifi/configure`.

2026-05-29 — The `goConfigNext()` function in the frontend originally did a fetch to `/api/wifi/config` to save configuration immediately. It was simplified to just navigate (no fetch) because the config is saved together with the WiFi credentials in `iniciarConexion()` (step 3). This avoids saving config without WiFi credentials (the user could exit the wizard with a partial config).

2026-05-26 — Bug root cause of "doesn't work by IP": iniciarServidorWeb() registered routes but never called server->begin(). The server existed in RAM but wasn't listening. Always verify that begin() is called at the end of the server setup function. The 3 mandatory steps for ESPAsyncWebServer: ws->onEvent() → server->addHandler(ws) → server->begin().

2026-05-26 — Native DHT11 is fragile on ESP32-S3 at 240MHz: micros() timings are very tight. Sensor response timeout must be ≥200µs (not 100µs). The bit 0/1 threshold must be 40µs (not 28µs). If it fails in production, consider using the Adafruit DHT library with disableInterrupts.

2026-05-26 — temperaturaActual/humedadActual must be initialized to -127.0/-1.0 (error sentinels), NOT to 0.0. The value 0.0 is indistinguishable from a real reading and confuses the LCD and menus.

2026-05-24 — DHT11 integrated across the entire firmware. LCD now has 5 pages (0-4), page 4 = DHT. CSV now has 10 columns. JSON WebSocket now includes dhtTemp and dhtHum. DHT polling is every 30s from Core 0 (does not block Core 1). temperaturaActual=-127.0 if sensor does not respond (guard in menus and LCD). StaticJsonDocument increased from 256 to 320 bytes.

2026-05-24 — New DHT11 module created (dht.h/dht.cpp). Follows the same pattern as ultrasonidos.h/cpp: free functions, globals in config, logs via Terminal. GPIO 4 for DATA. Pending integration into menus and FreeRTOS tasks.

2026-05-21 — First scan complete. Project is an ESP32-S3 firmware by Ruben Blasco Armengod. Key observations:
- All comments and user-facing text are in Spanish. Maintain Spanish for all new text.
- Global state model: ~30 extern globals in config.h/config.cpp. No namespacing or encapsulation.
- The web UI is embedded as PROGMEM HTML strings in web_pages.cpp — very large strings.
- Telemetry CSV appends every 2 hours. Auto-deletes at 8MB.
- TerminalHibrida extends Print — used as a drop-in replacement for Serial in most places.
- Login cookie token is random but stored in RAM only (lost on reboot — user must re-login).
- I2C_LCD addresses: LiquidCrystal_I2C(0x27, 16, 2). SDA=GPIO8, SCL=GPIO9 (non-default I2C pins).
- `main.ino:loop()` calls `vTaskDelete(NULL)` — this is intentional to kill the Arduino loop task after FreeRTOS tasks start.

